layout.description: Manually positioned 20 containers with shared safe height for efficient routing

power_management_info.description: Optimized for intelligent power management with shared safe height
power_management_info.routing: All movements route via shared_safe_height for collision avoidance
power_management_info.efficiency: Reduced position count from shared safe height approach

shared_safe_height.description:
Move the robot to a SHARED SAFE HEIGHT position.
This position should be:
- High enough to clear ALL containers in your workspace
- Positioned centrally to minimize travel time
- A "parking" position for safe movement between containers
- Clear of any obstacles or collision hazards
This single position will be used for safe transitions between all containers.

balance_position.description:
Move the robot to the BALANCE location where containers will be placed for measurement.
Position the gripper where it can place and retrieve containers on the balance.
This is the weighing/measurement station where each container will be processed.

balance_safe_height.description:
Move the robot to a SAFE HEIGHT above the balance.
This should be high enough to clear the balance and any containers on it.
Used for safe approach and departure from the balance during operations.
This is a safe intermediate position above the balance.

container_1_pickup.description:
Position the gripper to PICKUP Container #1.
The gripper should be positioned ready to close around the container for gripping.
Position where the robot will actually grab and lift the container.
Ensure the gripper is properly aligned for reliable pickup.
NOTE: The robot will approach this position via the shared safe height.
